The second text describes the 'Long-Term Debt-to-Equity Ratio,' a financial metric used to assess a company's financial leverage by comparing its long-term debt to its equity. These are distinct concepts from different domains (labor economics vs. corporate finance), hence they do not describe the same causal variable.
